<H1 class="h1" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">Asia Pacific - Private Wealth Manager Role</H1>

<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
The Private Wealth Manager serves as a Financial Advisor to high-net-worth and ultra-high-net-worth individuals, providing investment advice and solutions to meet their financial goals. The role requires broad financial knowledge and a variety of skills.
</p>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>Job Objectives</b></H2>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>Servicing of high-net-worth clients</li>
	<li>Has a specific geographic market focus by developing clients in one or two markets of greatest impact</li>
	<li>Partners with other businesses to facilitate client needs and maximize client relationships</li>
	<li>Provides clients with customized solutions by implementing a strategy that facilitates a breadth of offerings, including investment management, generational planning, banking and liability management</li>
	<li>Works as part of a team to develop and retain current client relationships</li>
	<li>Manages a client service officer or a client service associate who obtains investment information from clients to create and maintain client profiles</li>
	<li>Conducts proper due diligence and complies with regulatory matters</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>Core Knowledge and Skills Requirements</b></H2>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>Is an experienced wealth management advisor, preferably with more than five years of service</li>
	<li>Has an established book of business with a minimum of US $100 million of assets under management; the majority of client relationships should be greater than US $1 million</li>
	<li>Is independent, exhibits integrity, initiative, strong motivation and attention to detail</li>
	<li>Is fluent in English and the language of the prospective client market</li>
	<li>Has good presentation and communication skills and is a good listener</li>
	<li>Demonstrates an appropriate level of technical and professional skills and knowledge</li>
	<li>Recognizes and values individual uniqueness and differences, demonstrates client focus, respect for the individual, teamwork and responsible citizenship</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>Strategic Value of the Role</b></H2>
<ul style="margin-top: 3px;">
	<li>Serves as the primary point of contact with client</li>
	<li>Ensures client satisfaction and retention</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><b>Resources</b></H2>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
At Merrill Lynch Wealth Management, we offer a broad product platform and professional support that allows Private Wealth Managers to offer solutions designed to meet their clients&#39; financial needs.
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
Upon joining the company, Private Wealth Managers participate in a comprehensive Transition Program to familiarize them with sales-related sources and the wealth management process, various marketing tools, products and systems. Our powerful tools and resources are readily accessible from a state-of-the-art workstation. The Practice Management Consulting group is also available to work with Private Wealth Managers to improve performance through increased productivity, enhanced client satisfaction and development of business plans.
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">
Above all, there&#39;s the support private wealth managers receive from the entire organization, including management, product specialists and our award-winning research team.
</p>

